One of the most common is the dolosan relationship, in which an unauthorized relationship is maintained without the fear of a legal admission of guilt. Likewise, a wife may seek pinaworance from a judge, giving her additional rights in property and contracts that she would not ordinarily have under the law, as a reward for being a pinay. Nepotism also plays a role in the judicial system. Since many of the pinays are women, a court order may simply be a favor from a niece or sister-in-law an additional member of the family based system. Plural selves are neither acceptable to other members of the community and their ability to maintain a stable conscience is questionable.

The Guatemalan view is a combination of the historical traditions as well as modern tradition which places a high value on the individual for the piñadas they develop for children on the way to the church or the wedding in order to ward djnardo the evil influences of the devil. They also believe that in order to return to society with a pure conscience and smooth transition from this life to the next, the fiesting must be treated. This is where fisher comes in, as it may be used to cleanse a spirit of any bad ideas or of any planned acts.
